so first of all we have to understand mitm attack, here we have multiple types, in this we have interception.
The attacker must convince the client to send data to them instead of the true server. This is commonly done through 
ARP Poisoning (LAN): The attacker sends fake ARP messages on a local network to link their MAC address with the IP address of 
the legitimate default gateway.
The client's traffic is sent to the attacker.DNS Spoofing: The attacker poisons the DNS server, mapping the domain name
(e.g., bank.com) to the attacker's malicious IP address rather than the real server's IP.
Evil Twin Wi-Fi: The attacker creates a fake Wi-Fi hotspot with the same name as a legitimate one, making all traffic 
pass through the attacker's device.
